<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Containing Blocks - top, bottom, and left padding depend on ltr direction when ancestor is inline-level</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If the ancestor is inline-level, postioned absolute, and direction is ltr, the top/left of the containing block determines the top/left padding edges of the first box generated by the ancestor." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #s1
            {
                position: absolute;
                direction: ltr;
                display: inline;
                background: red;
                border: solid 3px black;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
            }
            #s2
            {
                position: absolute;
                padding-top: 10px;
                padding-left: 10px;
                background: green;
                width: 90px;
                height: 90px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if a black bordered box with a green background is visible and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <span id="s1">
            <span id="s2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
        </span>
    </body>
</html>